<br>
Also since you are only 54th I would advise you to get the best haste item that you can and to level up as fast as you can.  Level and haste do a lot for your ability to keep agro and are often overlooked by people who focus on weapons too much. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubrutultarewmarr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brutul Tarew Marr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Slayer of Whiners</span><br>  Posts: 704<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/15/02 4:36:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3559.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.blackcompany.cc/member_pics/45.jpg height=185 width=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: hmm</span><hr size=1> Where in the hell is Gorlab?  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
You want both.  That is my final answer for this topic.  Don't use an all-damage no-proc weapon, don't use a crap dps weapon with a good proc.  Balance them, use a little common sense, try stuff out and see how it works for you.  <br>
<br>
Velious aggro weapons =&gt;frostbringer, wavecrasher, willsapper, SoD.<br>
<br>
All have decent speed/ratio and a good aggro proc.  Look for the best combination of speed/ratio/proc that you can afford and get it.<br>
<br>
Enraging blow weapons own.  Went to NToV for the first time in like 3 months and I got to try out my Lammy v. 2.0 on the drakes and I swear you could just tank for the first 4 procs and then go afk for the rest of the fight (try to make it back for enrage <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).  In CT I got a double proc on my first round and immediately and with a primal/burrower spine wielding rog going all out on him, and me just standing there, I didn't lose aggro until the lizard was at half health.  Those weapons have it all, proc, stats, AND ratio, but they wouldn't be the godly weapons that they are without the proc.  There's basically 3 warrior weapons in Luclin.  If a warrior doesn't have two of them, he's trying to get them.  The main reason this is true is because they have the best proc in the game right now.  Sorry, I'm rambling. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6629>Brutul Vilesilencer</a><br>

